pageContext.claim: “Why didn't Biden get him [al-Baghdadi]? You know they were after him for eight years and never got him. ”
pageContext.analysis: This is unlikely. Al-Baghdadi became the leader of Al Qaeda in Iraq, which was then a failing organization, in 2006. He only gained global notoriety in 2013 after his militia took advantage of the chaos in Syria to build the Islamic State.
